external_knowledge:
'80s refers to the decade between 1980 and 1989;
"victorious teams" refers to the team winning the championship each year;
The crowd gathered around the Boston Celtics' matches refers to the average attendance at the games played by the Boston Celtics team.

- "Most recent team activity day" refers to the latest date recorded in the access logs; 
- "Members and their roles" mean the username and role of each user;
- "Teams they belong to" indicates the name of the team associated with each user.

sql:
SELECT t.name AS team_name, l.name AS league_name
FROM teams t
LEFT JOIN leagues l ON t.league = l.name;

SELECT t.name AS team_name, s.year AS season_year
FROM teams t
JOIN seasons s ON t.team_id = s.champion_team_id;

SELECT name, draft_year
FROM players
ORDER BY draft_year DESC, name ASC;

SELECT user_id, last_login_date
FROM users
WHERE team_id = (SELECT team_id FROM teams WHERE abbreviation = 'ATL');

